Accessing to Swestore files step by step

Salma Kazemi Rashed

21st of Aug, 2019¶

First We need to log in to the snic supr account as following:

The user name and the password of the Swestore account is the one that is determinded as following:

The simple way through the web browser is to access the files through the door of

https://webdav.swestore.se/snic/aits

by the username and password of swestore dCache provided in the SNIC SUPR account. Besides, we can also access files through the command line. However, we need to go through some steps before being able to access to Swestore files.

1) The first step is to apply for a grid personal license from>

https://www.digicert.com/

The proper link for lund university could be found here:

 https://snicdocs.nsc.liu.se/wiki/Grid_certificates

Click on the link as follows:

https://www.ldc.lu.se/tjanster/it-sakerhet/certifikat

Type "lund university" in the blank space:

Download the certificate file and save it.

2) After extracting the zip file, upload the certificate to SUPR snic to the personal information part.

3) Export the license from the browser (get a backup) in the form of *.p12 file.

4) convert the exported license to the private key and public key forms (*.pem) and save in the ~/.globus/ directory.

The goal is to end up with a .globus directory in our home directory, containing two files named "usercert.pem" and "userkey.pem"

To convert the ".p12" file to private and public key the following commands must be run:

Extract and protect the private key part of "export.p12":

openssl pkcs12 -nocerts -in ~/export.p12 -out ~/.globus/userkey.pem

export.p12 is the exported license file saved in home directory: "~/export.p12"

When asked for import password, specify the password specified when exporting the certificate bundle from your browser. The PEM pass phrase should be a new password that you need to provide whenever using the certificate for tasks like generating a proxy certificate. The output from this command will be similar to the following:

Enter Import Password: *******

verified OK

Enter PEM pass phrase: *******

Verifying - Enter PEM pass phrase: *******

Extract the public client certificate part of export.p12:

openssl pkcs12 -clcerts -nokeys -in ~/export.p12 -out ~/.globus/usercert.pem:

The output will be similar to the following:

Enter Import Password: *******

verified OK

Please Note that:

For your local system and the cluster systems this process should be done.

Now files are accessible through web browser by the username and password of the Swestore dCache account.

We can also access files through the lftp command tool.

Necessary commands for being able to access files through lftp toolkit would be:

arcproxy

The first command would automatically generate the proxy certificates in /tmp/ directory as x509up\_uxxxx which is needed to be initiated as the lftp variables.

set ssl:check-hostname true

set ssl:key-file /tmp/x509up\_uxxxx

ssl:cert-file /tmp/x509up\_uxxxx

lftp https://s_salka@webdav.swestore.se/snic/aits/.

It is fun to know that in this environment all bash commands work in the folder we run lftp command with the sign of "!" but not on the Swestore files!

Mostly we use "get" command for downloading the files we want and "put" for uploading to the Swestore!

Good luck!
